  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Personal Trainer",
  "description": "<p><u>Job description:</u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are looking for a passionate, driven &amp; experienced Personal Trainer to join the team at BBF GYM! As a Trainer at BBF, you will be supporting the team to elevate the business, grow together. Most importantly, providing clients with an excellent and truly satisfying experience.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Job requirements:</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Passionate in training and helping clients with their fitness journey</li>\n  <li>Self-driven and motivated to service clients</li>\n  <li>Able to commit to working closely with clients to achieve their goals</li>\n  <li>A good team player</li>\n  <li>Willing to accommodate clients schedule, weekends &amp; public holidays <em>if required</em></li>\n  <li>Flexible working schedule with good time management</li>\n  <li>Personal Training Certified and any relevant experience. 2 to 3 years in related field.</li>\n  <li>Patient and good customer service</li>\n  <li>Good sense of humour is a plus!</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Job responsibilities includes, but not limited to:</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct consultation and fitness assessment for clients</li>\n  <li>Develop training programmes (nutrition advice if needed) for clients to achieve their goals</li>\n  <li>Work closely with clients and the team</li>\n  <li>Create content with the team (social media &amp; tech savvy)</li>\n  <li>Guide and educate clients on equipment and training safety</li>\n  <li>Monitor/track clients progress and discuss how you can service them better</li>\n  <li>Provide accountability for clients</li>\n  <li>Maintain professional image for the team</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
